  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison reports on the Non-Resistance Convention. Radical and &quot;ultra&quot; resolutions were adopted. Henry C. Wright held public discussions with Nathaniel Colver. Colver showed a &quot;devilish spirit&quot; in the debates. Garrison has been busy moving into a house in Cambridgeport with a lease of two years. Garrison is in need of money; he has borrowed from both Samuel Philbrick and Francis Jackson. He asks George William Benson to obtain a loan for him of $300. Garrison had to pay $40 to release his brother James from the Navy Yard.</subfield>
